@RobertMurraySmith.  Just had our gas boiler replaced by a heat pump, which included having a new hot water cylinder installed.  The old H/W cylinder is only about 10 years old, it's reasonable well insulated and is 250L........so, is a H/W cylinder a good option for turning into a sand battery?  

Lots of questions around how I get the sand in, how I heat it up, how I get the heat out, what's a safe temperature to take it to, etc, etc.

It has the original coil used for heating it up (could that be how I get the heat out?).  It has the immersion heater still and there is a place for a second immersion heater to be added, plus there are the inlet and outlet pipes originally used for the hot water.

